{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κῶμος</b>, ὁ, <br /> <b>revel, carousal, merry-making</b>, εἰς δαῖτα θάλειαν καὶ χορὸν ἱμερόεντα καὶ ἐς φιλοκυδέα κ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “hymnus ad Mercurium” 481, compare 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 829, 940; πίνειν καὶ κώμῳ χρᾶσθαι 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.21, compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Alcestis” 804, etc.; κῶμοι καὶ εὐφροσύναι 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus 10.12; δεῖπνα καὶ σὺν αὐλητρίσι κῶμοι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 173d; ἑορταὶ καὶ κ. [prev. author] “R.” 573d \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; ἐν κώμῳ εἶναι, of a city, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 7.5.25; ἔρχεσθαί τισιν ἐπὶ κῶμον [prev. author] “Smp.” 2.1; ἐπὶ κῶμον βαδίζειν 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 1040 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; especially in honour of gods, τοῖς ἐν ἄστει Διονυσίοις ἡ πομπὴ.. καὶ ὁ κ. Legal cited in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.10, compare “IG” 2.971, etc.\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; κώμῳ θυραμάχοις τε πυγμαχίαισι Pratin.Lyric poetry 1.8; χοροῖς ἢ κώμοις Ὑακίνθου [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Helena” 1469 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> concrete, <b>band of revellers</b>, κ. εὐίου θεοῦ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ba.” 1167 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs</a>]; especially of the <b>procession</b> which celebrated a victor in games, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 5.22, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: generally, <b>rout, band</b>, κ. Ἐρινύων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1189 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; of an army, κ. ἀναυλότατος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 791 (Lyric poetry); κ. ἀσπιδηφόρος [prev. author] “Supp.” 390 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>band</b> of hunters, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Hipp.” 55 \">Refs</a>]; of maidens, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Tr.” 1184 \">Refs</a>]; of doves, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ion” 1197. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>the ode sung</b> at one of these festive processions, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 8.20, 70, “O.” 4.10, 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus 8.103; μελιγαρύων τέκτονες κώμων 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 3.5, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 104, 988 (both Lyric poetry). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G2970","accentedUnicode":"κῶμος","shortDef":"orgy, revelry, carousing","mediumDef":"orgy, revelry, carousing <br /><i>primarily</i> <b>a festive procession, a merry-making;</b> in NT <b>a revel, lewd, immoral feasting,</b> <ref='Rom.13.13'>Rom. 13:13;</ref> <ref='Gal.5.21'>Gal. 5:21;</ref> <ref='1Pe.4.3'>1Pet. 4:3</ref>*","stepGloss":"orgy","stepTransliteration":"kōmos","count":3,"_es_Definition":"parranda, borrachera, orgía, juerga, jolgorio","_zh_tw_Definition":"過度的宴樂 (羅 13:13; 加 5:21; 彼前 4:3)","_zh_Definition":"过度的宴乐 (罗 13:13; 加 5:21; 彼前 4:3)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"sự chè chén say sưa","_zh_tw_Gloss":"荒宴","_es_Gloss":"orgía","_zh_Gloss":"荒宴"}]}